ession splines, boosted regression trees, random forest, and maximum entropy. We then projected these models into 17 \"worst-case\" future climate scenarios for year 2070 to generate hypotheses about how the vampire bat distribution in North America might change in the future. Of the variables used in this analysis, minimum temperature of the coldest month had the highest variable importance using all 5 SDM approaches. These results suggest two potential near-future routes of vampire bat dispersal into the U.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Hayes, Mark A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Piaggio, Antoinette J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Russo, Danilo", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/56a42373a310e7deb4ec582c5b984f47", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/e4a1583f35b18d6725dd985744fae952fe65e276811978f0c1583f9d579a792f", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/SQ3FPGG6", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/SQ3FPGG6", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/4ecaea99a327a182e22b928fc90c0de9!/b358001-360700", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "2", "pages": "e0192887", "title": "PLOS ONE", "volume": "13"}, "alternate_identifiers"